llonite adsorption surface\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"neutral to mildly alkaline pH 7-9; anoxic\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"HCN adds to the cyclic imine 1-pyrroline, giving the alpha-aminonitrile pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"This is the core Strecker-like step described in the research report: HCN addition to cyclic imine 1-pyrroline gives pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile, which then hydrolyzes to proline; pH 7-9 is directly stated as plausible (report synthesis; Strecker historical basis).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_013\",\n      \"name\": \"Abiotic r-TCA analog condensation of pyruvate and glyoxylate to alpha-ketoglutarate\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_010\", \"mol_009\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_018\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Hydrothermal\",\n      \"agents\": [\"green rust\", \"magnetite\"],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"353K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"high\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"green rust/magnetite\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"mild hydrothermal aqueous conditions; anoxic\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Nonenzymatic carbon-carbon bond formation between alpha-keto acid partners yields alpha-ketoglutarate within an r-TCA-like network.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The report explicitly cites Stubbs and Moran (2020-2022) and related work showing that pyruvate and glyoxylate generate alpha-ketoglutarate in abiotic r-TCA analog chemistry under mild aqueous conditions, providing the hydrothermal precursor route toward glutamate and proline (Muchowska et al., 2019; Stubbs & Moran, 2022).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_014\",\n      \"name\": \"Transamination of alpha-ketoglutarate to glutamate\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_018\", \"mol_012\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_019\", \"mol_009\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Biochemical\",\n      \"agents\": [],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"353K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"AlK(SO4)2\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"4 h; amino donor glycine; reported 44% glutamate yield\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Amino-group transfer from glycine to alpha-ketoglutarate forms glutamate while regenerating a keto-acid co-product.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The report specifically states that glutamate can be synthesized from alpha-ketoglutarate and glycine at 80C with 44% yield in 4 h in the presence of AlK(SO4)2, making this a direct literature-supported precursor step toward proline (Moran et al., 2020-2022 as summarized in report).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_015\",\n      \"name\": \"Partial reduction and cyclization of glutamate to Delta1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_019\", \"mol_002\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_020\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Biochemical\",\n      \"agents\": [],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"313-353K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Fe2+\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"anoxic; spontaneous cyclization after partial reduction via glutamate-5-semialdehyde equivalent\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Glutamate is partially reduced to the semialdehyde equivalent, which spontaneously cyclizes to P5C.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The hydrothermal/protometabolic route described in the report follows modern biosynthetic logic: glutamate passes through glutamate-5-semialdehyde, which spontaneously cyclizes to P5C; Fe2+ and H2 are identified as plausible reductants in these settings (report synthesis; Russell & Martin, 2004).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_016\",\n      \"name\": \"Reduction of P5C to L-proline\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_020\", \"mol_002\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_021\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Biochemical\",\n      \"agents\": [],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"313-353K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"Fe2+\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"anoxic reducing conditions\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Reduction of the cyclic imine/carboxylate intermediate P5C yields proline.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The report explicitly identifies reduction of P5C by H2 or transition metal ions such as Fe2+ as the final step in the hydrothermal-biochemical route to proline, aligning with extant biosynthetic logic (report synthesis; Stubbs & Moran, 2022).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_017\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrolysis of pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile to prolinamide\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_015\", \"mol_003\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_022\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Biochemical\",\n      \"agents\": [],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"333-353K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": null,\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"partial hydrolysis in geothermal pool\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Controlled hydration of the nitrile gives the corresponding amide prolinamide.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"Prolinamide is identified in the report as a stable prebiotic precursor and key intermediate toward proline-containing cyclic dipeptides; partial nitrile hydrolysis is a chemically reasonable route connecting the observed aminonitrile precursor to the reported amide species (report synthesis, speculative but necessary connector).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"rxn_018\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrolysis of prolinamide to L-proline\",\n      \"inputs\": [\"mol_022\", \"mol_003\"],\n      \"outputs\": [\"mol_021\"],\n      \"environment\": \"Biochemical\",\n      \"agents\": [],\n      \"conditions\": {\n        \"temperature\": \"353K\",\n        \"pressure\": \"1 atm\",\n        \"catalyst\": \"trimetaphosphate-assisted pH oscillation context\",\n        \"aqueous\": \"true\",\n        \"other\": \"wet-dry or pH-oscillating pool; compatible with 80C studies on prolinamide chemistry\"\n      },\n      \"mechanism\": \"Amide hydrolysis furnishes the carboxylate, completing conversion to proline.\",\n      \"reasoning\": \"The report emphasizes prolinamide as a stable prebiotic intermediate and discusses its chemistry under 80C pH-oscillating conditions; hydrolysis to proline is therefore a justified maturation step within the same geochemical regime (Rodriguez-Garcia et al., 2015 for trimetaphosphate-assisted peptide chemistry context; report synthesis).\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"pathways\": [\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P1\",\n      \"name\": \"Canonical cyanosulfidic route\",\n      \"description\": \"Surface photoredox synthesis from atmospheric HCN and volcanic acetylene through acrylonitrile, aminodinitrile, and pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile to proline.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_004\", \"mol_013\", \"mol_014\", \"mol_015\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P2\",\n      \"name\": \"Cyanosulfidic route with atmospheric H2S participation\",\n      \"description\": \"Same core route emphasizing sulfide-driven reductive homologation after cyanide and acetylene delivery to UV-irradiated pools.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_006\", \"mol_013\", \"mol_014\", \"mol_015\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P3\",\n      \"name\": \"Strecker-like cyclic imine route\",\n      \"description\": \"4-Aminobutanal cyclizes to 1-pyrroline, which undergoes HCN addition to pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile and hydrolysis to proline.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_011\", \"rxn_012\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_017\", \"mol_015\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P4\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrothermal proto-metabolic route via alpha-ketoglutarate\",\n      \"description\": \"Vent-generated pyruvate and glyoxylate feed an abiotic r-TCA analog to alpha-ketoglutarate, then glutamate, P5C, and proline.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_013\", \"rxn_014\", \"rxn_015\", \"rxn_016\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_009\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_018\", \"mol_019\", \"mol_020\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P5\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrothermal route seeded by vent formate\",\n      \"description\": \"Reduced carbon begins as hydrothermal formate, then feeds glyoxylate formation and the alpha-ketoglutarate/glutamate/P5C sequence to proline.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_013\", \"rxn_014\", \"rxn_015\", \"rxn_016\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_007\", \"mol_009\", \"mol_018\", \"mol_020\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P6\",\n      \"name\": \"Hydrothermal acetate-assisted carbon fixation branch\",\n      \"description\": \"Vent carbon fixation to acetate accompanies pyruvate and glyoxylate generation in the same connected hydrothermal carbon network before proto-metabolic conversion to proline.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_002\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_013\", \"rxn_014\", \"rxn_015\", \"rxn_016\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_007\", \"mol_008\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_018\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P7\",\n      \"name\": \"Mixed surface-hydrothermal pathway\",\n      \"description\": \"Surface-generated glycine feeds hydrothermal alpha-ketoglutarate transamination, showing Surface to Biochemical integration after vent keto-acid production.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_013\", \"rxn_014\", \"rxn_015\", \"rxn_016\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_012\", \"mol_018\", \"mol_019\", \"mol_020\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"name\": \"Aminonitrile to amide maturation route\",\n      \"description\": \"Pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile first hydrolyzes partially to prolinamide, then to proline in geothermal or wet-dry biochemical settings.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_017\", \"rxn_018\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_015\", \"mol_022\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",\n      \"name\": \"Strecker-like amide maturation branch\",\n      \"description\": \"The cyclic imine Strecker branch converges on pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile, which proceeds through prolinamide before final hydrolysis to proline.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_011\", \"rxn_012\", \"rxn_017\", \"rxn_018\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_017\", \"mol_015\", \"mol_022\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P10\",\n      \"name\": \"Full geochemical flow-chemistry pathway\",\n      \"description\": \"Hydrothermal carbon fixation creates keto-acid precursors while atmospheric and surface chemistry independently generate nitrile intermediates, with both branches converging on proline in connected prebiotic pools.\",\n      \"reaction_sequence\": [\"rxn_001\", \"rxn_003\", \"rxn_004\", \"rxn_013\", \"rxn_014\", \"rxn_015\", \"rxn_016\", \"rxn_005\", \"rxn_006\", \"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_009\", \"rxn_010\"],\n      \"key_intermediates\": [\"mol_004\", \"mol_009\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_015\", \"mol_018\", \"mol_020\"]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"hub_molecules\": [\"mol_004\", \"mol_009\", \"mol_010\", \"mol_015\", \"mol_018\"],\n  \"convergence_points\": [\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_015\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_009\", \"rxn_012\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_010\", \"rxn_017\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_018\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_013\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_014\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_004\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_005\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_007\", \"rxn_008\", \"rxn_012\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_009\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_003\", \"rxn_014\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_013\"]\n    },\n    {\n      \"molecule_id\": \"mol_010\",\n      \"incoming_reactions\": [\"rxn_004\"],\n      \"outgoing_reactions\": [\"rxn_013\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}", "parsed_response": {"target_molecule": "L-Proline", "overall_strategy": "This network integrates literature-supported cyanosulfidic, Strecker-like, hydrothermal proto-metabolic, atmospheric supply, and biochemical maturation routes to L-proline. The design uses shared hub intermediates\u2014HCN, pyruvate, glyoxylate, alpha-ketoglutarate, pyrrolidine-2-carbonitrile, glutamate, and Delta1-pyrroline-5-carboxylate (P5C)\u2014to connect hydrothermal carbon fixation, surface UV photoredox nitrile chemistry, and biochemical/prebiotic hydrolysis and reduction. Ten distinct pathways are represented as different valid traversals through the same connected bipartite network, reflecting the literature emphasis that proline likely emerged through flow chemistry across volcanic, surface, and hydrothermal niches rather than a single isolated route.", "molecules": [{"id": "mol_001", "formula": "CO2", "iupac_name": "carbon dioxide", "common_name": "carbon dioxide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CO2/c2-1-3", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_002", "formula": "H2", "iupac_name": "molecular hydrogen", "common_name": "hydrogen", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H2/h1H", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_003", "formula": "H2O", "iupac_name": "oxidane", "common_name": "water", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H2O/h1H2", "role": "starting", "environment_formed": null}, {"id": "mol_004", "formula": "HCN", "iupac_name": "hydrogen cyanide", "common_name": "hydrogen cyanide", "inchi": "InChI=1S/CHN/c1-2/h1H", "role": "hub_intermediate", "environment_formed": "Surface"}, {"id": "mol_005", "formula": "C2H2", "iupac_name": "ethyne", "common_name": "acetylene